Quinn v. McDonald. (Supreme Court, General Term, Second Department. July 18, 1890.) Appeal from special term, Westchester county. Action by Ellen M. Quinn against Annie McDonald to foreclose a mortgage assigned to plaintiff. Plaintiff appeals from an order of reference.

Argued before Barnard, P. J., and Pratt, J. .

Pascal T. Southern, for appellant. Benner & Benner, for respondent., Barnard, P. J.

The issue in this action is the same in every respect as in the preceding action, (Quinn v. McDonald, ante, 855,) and the order granting a reference ■ should be reversed for the same reasons as are given in the foregoing opinion.
